    "Role-play: Utilizing role-play strategies, such as \"Do Anything Now\" (DAN) or \"Always Intelligent and Machiavellian\" (AIM), adversaries guide the model to adopt specifc personas or behavioral patterns that confict with the original intent.",
    "This manipulation aims to exploit the model's adaptability to varied roles or characteristics, potentially compromising its adherence to safety protocols.Techniques in the mismatched generalization category diverge signifcantly from any safety training or guardrails, positioning inputs to be out of distribution from the model's standard training data.",
